Switch disconnectors are load break disconnection devices. They shall â€”
(a) be rated for d.c. use;
(b) be rated according with Clause 4.3.4.2.3;
(c) conform with switch disconnector requirements of AS 60947.3 with utilization category d.c.-PV2;
(d) interrupt all live conductors simultaneously (i.e. have at least one pole per polarity);
(e) be capable of being secured in the open position;
(f) be an independent manual operation; and
(g) not be polarity sensitive.
